<p>When you are writing a formula using literal numbers, make sure the numbers you are using are the same data type as
    the variable they are being assigned to.</p>
<p>For example, if you are storing the result in a float, ensure that your literal numbers are using the 'f' suffix.
    Example:</p>
<pre><code class="language-csharp">int fahrenheit = 94;

